{
  "texts": [
    "Purple words indicate diseases, while black words indicate measurements.",
    "Circles are phenotypes colored by the association score, and boxes represent the most general categories.",
    "NS, not significant.",
    "We further trained models on sex-stratified subgroups (female versus male), with and without matching on demographics and visitrelated covariates, to identify sex-specific clinical predictors.",
    "Given evidence that sex may influence different pathways to AD diagnosis 24, 46, 47, it is important to consider how patient heterogeneity may impact the training, utility and interpretation of a prediction model."
  ]
}